My skin has never looked like this before.
It didn’t happen overnight. It came from doing small things that felt pointless at first— Washing my face even when I was tired. Sticking to what actually worked. Not switching routines every two weeks.
It came from learning when to leave my skin alone. When to hydrate more. When to stop overthinking it.
Things not to do: • Follow trends • Chase 10-step routines • Start over every time your skin isn’t perfect by day 3

This is Benefit’s Plushtint Moisturizing Matte Lip Tint in the shade Purrr — a soft fig lip color that gives blurred, hydrating, and long-wearing pigment.
It’s the perfect MLBB (my lips but better) tint for everyday wear — zero stickiness, just a soft matte finish and comfort all day.
Great for anyone looking for a clean girl lip combo, desi soft glam, or a low-maintenance lip tint that actually stays on.
#BenefitPlushtint #SoftFigLip #LipTintRoutine #MLBBLips #DesiBeauty #HydratingLipTint #NoLinerLook #MakeupThatLasts #SoftGlamMakeup #CleanGirlAesthetic #EverydayMakeup #MakeupReels #TikTokBeauty #DesiMakeupLook

There was a time I used to hide my curls… now I take my time with them.
This is my full curly hair routine: I start by shaking out the excess water, gently pat with a towel, detangle with my wet brush, then layer my leave-in, curl cream, and gel for definition + shine.
It’s not just about products — it’s about learning to care for what I once tried to change.
Tag someone growing their curls back. Save this for your next wash day. 🌀
